<paragraph id="D1539F6AFFACFF99FD54F9E162BCD1EB" blockId="6.[154,1434,1636,1692]" pageId="6" pageNumber="6">
Plate I All specimens come from the Shishtu 1 Formation, Upper Devonian, Frasnian. Niaz section, eastern Tabas, central 
<collectingCountry id="A9FBDFFAFFACFF99FACBF90162B0D1EB" box="[1384,1430,1668,1691]" name="Iran" pageId="6" pageNumber="6">Iran</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
<caption id="8593CFE2FFACFF99FF38F94165FED1AC" box="[155,728,1732,1756]" pageId="6" pageNumber="6" startId="6.[155,201,1732,1756]">
<paragraph id="D1539F6AFFACFF99FF38F94165FED1AC" blockId="6.[155,1437,1732,2076]" box="[155,728,1732,1756]" pageId="6" pageNumber="6">
Figs 1-12: 
<emphasis id="E3984378FFACFF99FEB6F9416510D1AC" box="[277,566,1732,1756]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="6">
<taxonomicName id="16ECE4E9FFACFF99FEB6F94166A1D1AB" authorityName="BASSLER" authorityYear="1952" box="[277,391,1732,1755]" class="Stenolaemata" family="Fistuliporidae" genus="Canutrypa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cystoporida" pageId="6" pageNumber="6" phylum="Bryozoa" rank="genus">Canutrypa</taxonomicName>
hemispheroidea
</emphasis>
(YANG, 1954).
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="D1539F6AFFACFF99FEB6F96164B2DF6C" blockId="6.[155,1437,1732,2076]" pageId="6" pageNumber="6">1: Lateral view of the colony (SMF 21.098). 2: Transverse section of the colony, polished slab (SMF 21.098). 3: Transverse thin section of the colony (SMF 21.097). 4: Longitudinal thin section of multilayered colony (SMF 21.088). 5-6: Longitudinal thin section of multilayered colony showing autozooecial chambers, hemicylindrical cystlike structures and vesicular skeleton (SMF 21.084). 7: Tangential thin section showing macula consisting of vesicle skeleton (SMF 21.087). 8: Longitudinal thin section of multilayered colony showing autozooecial chambers, hemicylindrical cystlike structures and vesicular skeleton between autozooecia and in macula (SMF 21.097). 9: Longitudinal thin section showing hemicylindrical cystlike structure in autozooecial chamber (SMF 21.088). 10: Tangential thin section showing autozooecial apertures and vesicles (SMF 21.086). 11-12: Shallow tangential thin section showing autozooecial apertures, lunaria and extensively developed granular skeleton (SMF 21.093).</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="99F6CCE1FFA2FF97FF34FE846208D609" pageId="8" pageNumber="8" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph id="D1539F6AFFA2FF97FF34FE84665BD649" blockId="8.[151,757,257,953]" pageId="8" pageNumber="8">
<emphasis id="E3984378FFA2FF97FF34FE846622D669" bold="true" box="[151,260,257,281]" pageId="8" pageNumber="8">Material:</emphasis>
Four thin sections of two colonies 
<collectionCode id="B7FD07AFFFA2FF97FD1CFE8465D2D669" box="[703,756,257,281]" country="Germany" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34838" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34838" name="Forschungsinstitut und Natur-Museum Senckenberg" pageId="8" pageNumber="8">SMF</collectionCode>
21.100- 
<collectionCode id="B7FD07AFFFA2FF97FF53FEA46603D649" box="[240,293,289,313]" country="Germany" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34838" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34838" name="Forschungsinstitut und Natur-Museum Senckenberg" pageId="8" pageNumber="8">SMF</collectionCode>
21.103.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D1539F6AFFA2FF97FF34FEC4659AD5A9" blockId="8.[151,757,257,953]" pageId="8" pageNumber="8">
<emphasis id="E3984378FFA2FF97FF34FEC466A9D629" bold="true" box="[151,399,321,345]" pageId="8" pageNumber="8">Exterior description:</emphasis>
Reticulate colonies, composed of undulating branches and joined by dissepiments. Branches oval in transversal section. Fenestrules circular to oval. Autozooecia arranged in 3 to 4 rows on the branches. Dissepiments short. Autozooecial apertures circular, 4-7 spaced per length of a fenestrule, containing 10-12 long styles. Microstyles on the reverse surface common, irregularly and densely spaced, originating from interior granular skeleton, 
<quantity id="1614328FFFA2FF97FE1BFDC4654DD529" box="[440,619,577,601]" metricMagnitude="-5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" metricValueMax="1.5" metricValueMin="0.5" pageId="8" pageNumber="8" unit="mm" value="0.01" valueMax="0.015" valueMin="0.005">
<geoCoordinate id="B4D8F9ADFFA2FF97FE1BFDC466D3D529" box="[440,501,577,601]" degrees="0.005" direction="north" orientation="latitude" pageId="8" pageNumber="8" precision="55" value="0.005">0.005</geoCoordinate>
<geoCoordinate id="B4D8F9ADFFA2FF97FE56FDC4651FD529" box="[501,569,577,601]" degrees="0.015" direction="west" orientation="longitude" pageId="8" pageNumber="8" precision="55" value="-0.015">-0.015</geoCoordinate>
mm
</quantity>
in diameter. 
<collectingRegion id="13285188FFA2FF97FF34FDE467C1D509" box="[151,231,609,633]" country="Oman" name="Ad Dakhiliyah" pageId="8" pageNumber="8">Interior</collectingRegion>
granular skeleton variable in thickness, usually well-developed, continuous in microstyles. Extrazooidal skeleton finely laminated, well-developed on reverse side. Branch reverse side carrying distinct striation.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D1539F6AFFA2FF97FF34FD646208D609" blockId="8.[151,757,257,953]" lastBlockId="8.[831,1437,257,953]" pageId="8" pageNumber="8">
<emphasis id="E3984378FFA2FF97FF34FD6466A4D589" bold="true" box="[151,386,737,761]" pageId="8" pageNumber="8">
<collectingRegion id="13285188FFA2FF97FF34FD6467D7D589" box="[151,241,737,761]" country="Oman" name="Ad Dakhiliyah" pageId="8" pageNumber="8">Interior</collectingRegion>
description:
</emphasis>
Autozooecial chambers relatively short, deep, displaying rhombic shape in mid tangential section; elongate parallel to branch length; aperture positioned at distal to distoabaxial end of chamber; with moderately long vestibule. Hemisepta absent. Tubes connecting endozonal zooecial chambers with the obverse surface present, 3-7 spaced between adjacent apertures, 
<quantity id="1614328FFFA2FF97FC10FE84634ED669" box="[947,1128,257,281]" metricMagnitude="-5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.25" metricValueMax="3.5" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="8" pageNumber="8" unit="mm" value="0.0225" valueMax="0.035" valueMin="0.01">
<geoCoordinate id="B4D8F9ADFFA2FF97FC10FE8464D7D669" box="[947,1009,257,281]" degrees="0.010" direction="north" orientation="latitude" pageId="8" pageNumber="8" precision="55" value="0.01">0.010</geoCoordinate>
<geoCoordinate id="B4D8F9ADFFA2FF97FC52FE846312D669" box="[1009,1076,257,281]" degrees="0.035" direction="west" orientation="longitude" pageId="8" pageNumber="8" precision="55" value="-0.035">-0.035</geoCoordinate>
mm
</quantity>
in diameter. Heterozooecia are brood chambers represented by enlarged zooecia, rounded to oval in mid tangential section, situated on branches near dissepiments, 
<quantity id="1614328FFFA2FF97FBD2FEE463CAD609" box="[1137,1260,353,377]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" metricValueMax="3.0" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="8" pageNumber="8" unit="mm" value="0.25" valueMax="0.3" valueMin="0.2">0.2-0.3 mm</quantity>
wide.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="99F6CCE1FFA2FF95FCE3FE0465E5D649" lastPageId="10" lastPageNumber="10" pageId="8" pageNumber="8" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="D1539F6AFFA2FF97FCE3FE046394D4E9" blockId="8.[831,1437,257,953]" pageId="8" pageNumber="8">
<emphasis id="E3984378FFA2FF97FCE3FE046496D6E9" bold="true" box="[832,944,385,409]" pageId="8" pageNumber="8">Remarks:</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="16ECE4E9FFA2FF97FC1EFE07625BD6E9" authority="FRITZ, 1938" authorityName="FRITZ" authorityYear="1938" box="[957,1405,385,409]" class="Stenolaemata" family="Semicosciniidae" genus="Anastomopora" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Fenestrida" pageId="8" pageNumber="8" phylum="Bryozoa" rank="species" species="quebecensis">
<emphasis id="E3984378FFA2FF97FC1EFE0763CFD6E9" box="[957,1257,385,409]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="8">Anastomopora quebecensis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="B57DE29BFFA2FF97FB55FE07625BD6E9" author="FRITZ" box="[1270,1405,385,409]" pageId="8" pageNumber="8" pagination="87 - 100" refId="ref7218" refString="FRITZ, M. A. (1938) - Devonian Bryozoa of Gaspe. Bulletins of American Paleontology, 24 (80): 87 - 100." type="journal article" year="1938">FRITZ, 1938</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="16ECE4E9FFA2FF97FC1FFE27620CD6C9" authority="MCNAIR, 1937" authorityName="MCNAIR" authorityYear="1937" box="[956,1322,417,441]" class="Stenolaemata" family="Semicosciniidae" genus="Anastomopora" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Fenestrida" pageId="8" pageNumber="8" phylum="Bryozoa" rank="species" species="petoskeyensis">
<emphasis id="E3984378FFA2FF97FC1FFE276355D6C9" box="[956,1139,417,441]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="8">A. petoskeyensis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="B57DE29BFFA2FF97FB21FE27620CD6C9" author="MCNAIR" box="[1154,1322,417,441]" pageId="8" pageNumber="8" pagination="103 - 170" refId="ref7486" refString="MCNAIR, A. H. (1937) - Cryptostomatous Bryozoa from the Middle Devonian Traverse Group of Michigan. Contributions from the Museum of Paleontology, University of Michigan, 5: 103 - 170." type="journal article" year="1937">MCNAIR, 1937</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
from the Traverse Group(Middle Devonian, Givetian)of 
<collectingRegion id="13285188FFA2FF97FA8CFE4462BED6A9" box="[1327,1432,449,473]" country="United States of America" name="Michigan" pageId="8" pageNumber="8">Michigan</collectingRegion>
, but differs from it in having narrower branches (
<quantity id="1614328FFFA2FF97FAC0FE646487D569" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.65" metricValueMax="7.5" metricValueMin="5.8" pageId="8" pageNumber="8" unit="mm" value="0.665" valueMax="0.75" valueMin="0.58">0.58- 0.75 mm</quantity>
vs. 0.4-1.0 mm in 
<taxonomicName id="16ECE4E9FFA2FF97FBDFFD87645FD549" authority="MCNAIR, 1937" authorityName="MCNAIR" authorityYear="1937" class="Stenolaemata" family="Semicosciniidae" genus="Anastomopora" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Fenestrida" pageId="8" pageNumber="8" phylum="Bryozoa" rank="species" species="petoskeyensis">
<emphasis id="E3984378FFA2FF97FBDFFD876208D569" box="[1148,1326,513,537]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="8">A. petoskeyensis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="B57DE29BFFA2FF97FA9BFD87645FD549" author="MCNAIR" pageId="8" pageNumber="8" pagination="103 - 170" refId="ref7486" refString="MCNAIR, A. H. (1937) - Cryptostomatous Bryozoa from the Middle Devonian Traverse Group of Michigan. Contributions from the Museum of Paleontology, University of Michigan, 5: 103 - 170." type="journal article" year="1937">MCNAIR, 1937</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
), and in shorter and wider fenestrules (average fenestrule length 
<quantity id="1614328FFFA2FF97FC5BFDC4636FD529" box="[1016,1097,577,601]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.0" pageId="8" pageNumber="8" unit="mm" value="0.8">0.8 mm</quantity>
vs. 
<quantity id="1614328FFFA2FF97FBD6FDC463E3D529" box="[1141,1221,577,601]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.0" pageId="8" pageNumber="8" unit="mm" value="0.9">0.9 mm</quantity>
in 
<taxonomicName id="16ECE4E9FFA2FF97FB44FDC762B3D529" authorityName="MCNAIR" authorityYear="1937" box="[1255,1429,577,601]" class="Stenolaemata" family="Semicosciniidae" genus="Anastomopora" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Fenestrida" pageId="8" pageNumber="8" phylum="Bryozoa" rank="species" species="petoskeyensis">
<emphasis id="E3984378FFA2FF97FB44FDC762B3D529" box="[1255,1429,577,601]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="8">A. petoskeyensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and average fenestrule width 0.52 vs. 
<quantity id="1614328FFFA2FF97FAADFDE46251D509" box="[1294,1399,609,633]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.5" pageId="8" pageNumber="8" unit="mm" value="0.45">0.45 mm</quantity>
in 
<taxonomicName id="16ECE4E9FFA2FF97FCE3FD0764DCD5E9" authorityName="MCNAIR" authorityYear="1937" box="[832,1018,641,665]" class="Stenolaemata" family="Semicosciniidae" genus="Anastomopora" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Fenestrida" pageId="8" pageNumber="8" phylum="Bryozoa" rank="species" species="petoskeyensis">
<emphasis id="E3984378FFA2FF97FCE3FD0764DCD5E9" box="[832,1018,641,665]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="8">A. petoskeyensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). Unfortunately, both species were described externally. 
<taxonomicName id="16ECE4E9FFA2FF97FB84FD276452D5A9" authority="FRITZ, 1938" authorityName="FRITZ" authorityYear="1938" class="Stenolaemata" family="Semicosciniidae" genus="Anastomopora" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Fenestrida" pageId="8" pageNumber="8" phylum="Bryozoa" rank="species" species="quebecensis">
<emphasis id="E3984378FFA2FF97FB84FD276268D5C9" box="[1063,1358,673,697]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="8">Anastomopora quebecensis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="B57DE29BFFA2FF97FAF4FD276452D5A9" author="FRITZ" pageId="8" pageNumber="8" pagination="87 - 100" refId="ref7218" refString="FRITZ, M. A. (1938) - Devonian Bryozoa of Gaspe. Bulletins of American Paleontology, 24 (80): 87 - 100." type="journal article" year="1938">FRITZ, 1938</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to 
<emphasis id="E3984378FFA2FF97FC5DFD47634DD5A9" box="[1022,1131,705,729]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="8">A. stellata</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="B57DE29BFFA2FF97FBDAFD47627DD5A9" author="KRASNOPEEVA &amp; Bryozoans of the Middle" box="[1145,1371,705,729]" pageId="8" pageNumber="8" pagination="43 - 84" refId="ref7418" refString="KRASNOPEEVA, P. S. (1935) - Bryozoans of the Middle and Devonian of Altai. Materialy po geologii Zapadno- Sibirskogo Kraya, 20: 43 - 84 [in Russian]." type="journal article" year="1935">KRASNOPEEVA, 1935</bibRefCitation>
) from the Upper Devonian (Frasnian) of 
<collectingRegion id="13285188FFA2FF97FB66FD6463DCD589" box="[1221,1274,737,761]" country="Russia" name="Altay" pageId="8" pageNumber="8">Altai</collectingRegion>
in its internal morphology (zooecial shape, apertural styles), but differs in wider branches and larger fenestrules (branch width 
<quantity id="1614328FFFA2FF97FC9CFCC464F0D429" box="[831,982,833,857]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.65" metricValueMax="7.5" metricValueMin="5.8" pageId="8" pageNumber="8" unit="mm" value="0.665" valueMax="0.75" valueMin="0.58">0.58-0.75 mm</quantity>
vs. 
<quantity id="1614328FFFA2FF97FBA7FCC463B8D429" box="[1028,1182,833,857]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.85" metricValueMax="4.5" metricValueMin="3.2" pageId="8" pageNumber="8" unit="mm" value="0.385" valueMax="0.45" valueMin="0.32">0.32-0.45 mm</quantity>
, fenestrule length 
<quantity id="1614328FFFA2FF97FAC6FCC46487D409" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.25" metricValueMax="10.5" metricValueMin="6.0" pageId="8" pageNumber="8" unit="mm" value="0.825" valueMax="1.05" valueMin="0.6">0.60- 1.05 mm</quantity>
vs. 
<quantity id="1614328FFFA2FF97FC70FCE46348D409" box="[979,1134,865,889]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.65" metricValueMax="7.199999999999999" metricValueMin="6.1" pageId="8" pageNumber="8" unit="mm" value="0.665" valueMax="0.72" valueMin="0.61">0.61-0.72 mm</quantity>
, and fenestrule width 0.32- 0.70 vs. 
<quantity id="1614328FFFA2FF97FC39FC046316D4E9" box="[922,1072,897,921]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.6" metricValueMax="2.9" metricValueMin="2.3" pageId="8" pageNumber="8" unit="mm" value="0.26" valueMax="0.29" valueMin="0.23">0.23-0.29 mm</quantity>
<emphasis id="E3984378FFA2FF97FB95FC076385D4E9" box="[1078,1187,897,921]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="8">A. stellata</emphasis>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D1539F6AFFA2FF97FC9CFC2462BAD4C9" blockId="8.[831,1437,257,953]" box="[831,1436,929,953]" pageId="8" pageNumber="8">
